{
    "title": "Triadic Emergent Duality: 14+ Candidate Dualities Across 6 Algebraic Layers",
    "version": "0.2.1",
    "description": "A formal ontological framework in which conceptual complexity emerges from 14+ candidate dualities organized across 6 algebraic layers (Boolean, Fuzzy, Ordinal, Modal, Trivalent, Probabilistic). Grounded in 72 semantic primitives connected by a DAG of 133+ dependency edges. Evaluated through domain analysis (8 disciplines + 3 negative controls, DVS metric), Bayesian model comparison (BF=121.4), and neurosymbolic learning (GPT-2 Medium + 72-bit triadic head, 90.8% accuracy).",
